<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,151,738]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
REMARKS: The family placement is provisional. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart, P. - J. - M." box="[873,1140,450,476]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref130458" refString="Macquart, P. - J. - M. (1835) Histoire naturelle des insectes. Dipteres. Tome deuxieme. N. E. Roret, Paris. 703 or 710 pp. [1 April] [Dated from Evenhuis (1997: 512).]" type="book" year="1835">Macquart (1835: 437)</bibRefCitation>
placed the 
<typeStatus box="[1289,1339,450,476]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[205,296,488,513]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Boisduvalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilans">
<emphasis box="[205,296,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">rutilans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fallen, 1810" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1810" box="[462,704,488,514]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Ortalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[462,545,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Ortalis</emphasis>
Fallén, 1810
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName box="[721,838,488,514]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ulidiidae</taxonomicName>
], 
<bibRefCitation author="Loew, H." box="[860,1061,488,514]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref130207" refString="Loew, H. (1873) Monographs of the Diptera of North America. Part III. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections 11 [= No. 256], vii + 351 + XIII pp. [December]" type="book" year="1873">Loew (1873: 18)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized this genus-group name with 
<taxonomicName authority="Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[344,763,525,551]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Rivellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[344,435,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Rivellia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Robineau-Desvoidy, J. - B." box="[448,763,525,551]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref137424" refString="Robineau-Desvoidy, J. - B. (1830) Essai sur les myodaires. Memoires presentes par divers savans a l'Academie Royale des Sciences de l'Institut de France (Sciences Mathematiques et Physiques), (2) 2, 813 pp. [6 June] [Date recorded as received in Bibliographie de la France.]" type="book" year="1830">Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus has not been treated in the major regional 
<taxonomicName box="[205,293,562,588]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
catalogs and comprises five species: one 
<collectingRegion box="[791,890,562,588]" country="Egypt" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Oriental</collectingRegion>
, two Afrotropical, and two 
<emphasis box="[1219,1375,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">patria ignota</emphasis>
. The genus-group name is not to be found in the platystomatid chapters of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1116,1212,600,626]" country="Egypt" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Oriental</collectingRegion>
catalog (
<bibRefCitation author="Steyskal, G. C." pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="135 - 164" refId="ref142456" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1977) Family Platystomatidae, pp. 135 - 164. In: Delfinado, M. D. &amp; Hardy, D. E. (eds.), A catalog of the Diptera of the Oriental Region. Volume III. Suborder Cyclorrhapha (excluding Division Aschiza). University Press of Hawaii, Honolulu. x + 854 pp. [4 November] [Dated from Evenhuis (2008 b).]" type="book chapter" year="1977">Steyskal, 1977</bibRefCitation>
) or Afrotropical catalog (
<bibRefCitation author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[600,787,637,663]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="563 - 574" refId="ref142541" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1980) Family Platystomatidae, pp. 563 - 574. In: Crosskey, R. W. (ed.), Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region. British Museum (Natural History), London. 1437 pp. [20 July] [Dated from Evenhuis (2008 b).]" type="book chapter" year="1980">Steyskal, 1980</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hendel, F." box="[816,1078,637,663]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 179" refId="ref126606" refString="Hendel, F. (1914 b) Diptera. Fam. Muscaridae. Subfam. Platystominae. Genera Insectorum, 157, 1 - 179. [10 June] [For dating of this series, see Evenhuis (1994).]" type="journal article" year="1914">Hendel (1914b: 169)</bibRefCitation>
did treat the genus [in his “Platystominae”] and designated 
<taxonomicName authority="Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[599,1155,674,700]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Boisduvalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilans">
<emphasis box="[599,838,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Boisduvalia rutilans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Robineau-Desvoidy, J. - B." box="[847,1155,674,700]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref137424" refString="Robineau-Desvoidy, J. - B. (1830) Essai sur les myodaires. Memoires presentes par divers savans a l'Academie Royale des Sciences de l'Institut de France (Sciences Mathematiques et Physiques), (2) 2, 813 pp. [6 June] [Date recorded as received in Bibliographie de la France.]" type="book" year="1830">Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[1196,1246,674,700]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
species but this was later than the designation in d’Orbigny (1842a).
</paragraph>
